The paper deals with multi-robot path planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithmic framework presented in the paper involves optimization techniques and the use of discretization, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves centralized planning, which is a characteristic of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the framework in solving complex problems, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the performance of the algorithm, which is related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
